  <!--19-->Bred for Battle x3    </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font face="Haettenschweiler, Tahoma, Arial, sans-serif" size="5" COLOR="#000000">Strategy</Font></TD><TD><font face="Arial, sans-serif" size="2">This is the first deck I have ever made. I just started playing June 16th at the ROTEL pre-release; in fact, the first round game was my first game ever. I made this deck with my existing collection, which I put in the description of this deck. At the tournament I learned that Uruk-Hai kick some A-$$. <br />
<br />
My strategy is limited as is my experience but what I do is I like to go second so my opponent has to get my site 4 out. At that time I try to slow him down a lot with my nasty orc&#39;s and sic uruk-hai minions. After I slow him down in the mid to late sites I either stay with him move for move or I surge past him and deploy more and more companions so I can just blow through anything he try&#8217;s to put in my way. Yes I do lose companions but getting frodo across the line is all that matters.<br />
<br />
I would really like any tips you could give me. Also any cards you think I should try to get would help. Any guidance you can give would be greatly appreciated. Thanks.<br />
<br />
<br />
Sean &quot;Tyrpotix&quot; Miller<br />
